<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-02-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-02-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="321" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d321">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Dawson</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Dapartment of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-02-06"><hi rend="italic">February 6,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 46.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose the President’s full powers
                            authorizing you to sign the protocol with reference to the collection
                            and disbursement by the United States of the custom revenues of the
                            Dominican Republic, and confirm the telegram which I sent to you this
                            morning in the following language: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>The President has to-day telegraphed the President of Santo
                                    Domingo full powers for you to sign protocol. See him and sign
                                    at once.</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>